  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Embedded Software Engineer (satellite)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Our esteem client is looking for embedded software Engineers to join the organization. Successful Candidate will be involved in</strong> <strong>space , satellites and remote imagining projects. </strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Involved in space , satellites and remote imagining projects. </li><li>Work with engineers and system architects to obtain product features from analysis to deployment phases.</li><li>Implement the design in C and unit test all the software components.</li><li>Verify and validate software system on target hardware.</li><li>Perform software maintenance and advise users on the deployed software.</li><li>Participate in the definition of the future products.</li><li>Enhance infrastructures to hit performance and reliability metrics.</li><li>Drive data-driven decisions through metrics, experimentation, and experience.</li><li>Problem solving, thinking through everything from user experience, data models, scalability, operability, and ongoing metrics.</li><li>Provide guidance to teammates contributing to the growth of the team.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge in Electrical or Computer Engineering or equivalent</li><li>Experience in embedded system software development, RTOS and/or Linux.</li><li>Knowledge of low-level device drivers like CAN, UART or SPI.</li><li>Proficient in C/C++ programming</li><li> Understanding of unit testing.</li><li>Experience in agile software development and embedded system product development from power-on to full functional system.</li><li>Understands hardware, able to read schematics and data sheets.</li></ul><p>To Apply or find out more information on this role, please email us or send in your updated resume to: shelly.tan@starcareerconsulting.com<br /></p><p>Shelly Tan Bee Leng (Reg. No. R2199458)</p><p>STAR CAREER CONSULTING PTE LTD (EA License: 20C0353)</p>",
